Campus Tour<br></a></li>
</ul>
<h2>About Our Campus<br>
</h2>

<h3>Buildings &amp; Facilities<br>
</h3>
<p>Our <a href="http://www.seas.harvard.edu/about-seas/map-directions/buildings" class="internal-link" title="Buildings">world class facilities provide</a> nearly 400,000 square
feet of interconnected labs, classrooms, clusters, and offices designed
to encourage researchers and students to cross boundaries and
collaborate.</p>
<h3>Main Administration<br>
</h3>
<p>Pierce Hall, located at 29 Oxford Street is the
<a href="http://www.seas.harvard.edu/administration" class="internal-link" title="Administration">administrative center</a> of SEAS, housing the Deans'
Offices, Student Services, and other administrative offices. In addition, SEAS-dedicated space in the Northwest Building also houses select functions (accounting and budgeting, procurement, and research administration).</p>
<h2>
<a name="maps"></a>Construction Updates<br>
</h2>
<p>
For the latest on nearby construction projects visit:</p>
<ul><li><a class="external-link" href="http://www.construction.harvard.edu/">http://www.construction.harvard.edu/</a></li></ul>
